th2_oate@csd.uwe.ac.uk (Tom Oates) writes:

> If someone sends me a message encrypted using v2.0, can I decrypt it
> using v2.1?

Yes.

> And vice versa.

Almost. Version 2.1 of PGP supports signed human-readable messages.
You won't be able to check the signature of such messages with PGP
2.0, because it does not support this feature. Otherwise everything
else is compatible.

> * Email to: th2_oate@uk.ac.uwe.csd     * PGP 2.0 Key available upon request. *

I am collecting public keys. Please consider this a request.

